{
  "stem": "15962.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There was, during our stay there, a revolt of that Sonderkommando, where they were able to get some rifles and armed themselves with all sorts of pipes and so on and staged an uprising in one of the crematorias.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But they were all killed eventually by the overwhelming superiority of SS.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But they were able to injure or kill a few guards.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But that's all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] Strangely enough, I don't really remember too much about other of the 89 boys.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Just, at that time, that six months is-- is a somewhat of a blur.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I remember, where I worked, that there was some only Poles who were my superior prisoners-- that the Poles really hated Jews and that the Jews were the lowest of the lowest, except the Russian war prisoners, who were treated much worse than anybody else.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they were tortured and not given any food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was a hierarchy in the camp-- that the most privileged were the German-- the real criminals who started Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had black triangles.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were-- every group, or-- or nationality or religion, had their special signs.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Jews had their Yellow Star of David.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were-- these were not Jewish Poles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not these that I worked with in-- in the-- in the family camp, there were only Jews from Theresienstadt, which was 90% Czechs-- some Germans, some Dutch-- very few Germans, very few Dutch, but mostly Czechs.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Slowly, we were taken out of this barrack number 13 and placed in-- amongst the other people in the camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as labor needs occurred in other camps, some of the boys-- this 89-- were shipped elsewhere, either in Auschwitz I, the main camp, or to completely elsewhere.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the group dwindled.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
